Site dedicated to all things Genis-Vell and Phyla-Vell. Former Captains Marvel and son and daughter of the original one, Mar-Vell. summary: Pitch for a “Miss Marvel” solo movie: We start off with a flashback to 7-year-old Kamala Khan. Kamala’s mom tells her a true...
body:
Pitch for a “Miss Marvel” solo movie:

We start off with a flashback to 7-year-old Kamala Khan. Kamala’s mom tells her a true story about how Captain Marvel saved her and Kamala’s father from a Skrull invasion (all references to the upcoming Captain Marvel movie). Kamala is amazed by the story, which leads to her fascination with superheroes throughout her childhood.

Cut to present-day. 17-year-old Kamala Khan is an average student who is a minor online celebrity. She’s a YouTuber under the name “Miss Marvel” (obviously named after Carol) and she mainly vlogs about superhero business. Although she’s happy to be vlogging about heroes, part of her wants to be one. 

Around the same time, Carol Danvers is the new head of the Avengers,  following the events of Infinity War (I’m assuming that Tony and Steve didn’t make it). When the main villain, Chen Lu / Radioactive Man, is spotted outside New York City, Carol decides to go after him alone. This results in a fight scene where she is “killed” (spoilers: she’s not dead). News of Captain Marvel’s death goes viral quickly. 

Kamala is devastated by the news and, against her best friend Nakia’s warnings, goes after Radioactive Man on her own. While out, she gets distracted by several loud screams nearby. She runs over and sees the area has been covered by Terrigen mist as a result of a Terrigen bomb activated by Radioactive Man. Kamala rescues a few civilians before getting hit by the mist, activating Terrigenesis. 

After emerging from the process, she realizes she’s gained the ability to change her body into any shape she wants. She tells Nakia this and we get a montage of Nakia helping Kamala gain control of her powers (think of Nakia as the Ned Leeds of the movie). 

Despite her initial fears, Kamala sees her new powers as a sign that she should become a superhero. We then get a joke along these lines:

Kamala: “From now on…you can call me…Miss Marvel.”

Nakia: “Your superhero name…is your YouTube username? Can’t you be more creative?” 

So while the main story of Kamala and Nakia going after Radioactive Man is happening, we learn that Carol survived the encounter with Radioactive Man and is recuperating while in hiding. Carol also goes after him, resulting in her crossing paths with Kamala. 

Carol is initially dismissive of Kamala, believing that she’s just a kid who is in way over her head, but after seeing Kamala handle herself in a fight, Carol decides to team up with her. Of course, this leads to the final confrontation with Radioactive Man, in which Kamala defeats him. 

Carol says Kamala is pretty good (for a kid) and contemplates adding her to the Avengers, which blows Kamala’s mind. Carol says she’ll bring the topic up to the other Avengers to see what they’ll say. Before she goes, Kamala asks for a favor.

The movie ends with one of Kamala’s YouTube vlogs, but Carol appears as a surprise guest. The video is called “I MET CAPTAIN MARVEL TODAY (not clickbait)” and although the video is about her, during the interview, Carol talks about how awesome Miss Marvel is. 

Mid-credits scene: Kamala is reading fanfiction about Miss Marvel (after her superhero persona went viral after the interview with Carol) and sees that she’s being shipped with someone called Silk. Kamala says, “Who the heck is Silk”?, ending the scene.

summary: AoS, A4, and Captain Marvel Theory
body:
AoS, A4, and Captain Marvel Theory

SPOILER WARNING FOR IFINITY WAR AND AGENTS OF SHIELD

Okay, so season five of Agents of SHIELD has ended with the death of Fitz (There goes my favorite ship #FitzSimmions) and Coulson in Tahiti waiting for his death (IRONY). I started to think of how they can come back (Coulson doesn’t want to but he better come back, dammit). TAHITI (The program not the actual place) was how Coulson was resseracted after being stabbed by Loki in The Avengers. TAHITI uses the blood of the Kree to bring people back from the dead. So that’s all you need right? Well, yeah but it’s a matter of finding it. Kree don’t live on Midgard and you can’t just steal one and take its blood. But there is one person who could give up Kree blood. That’s the Kree superhero Captain Marvel. She probably knows Coulson and would want to help him and his team. Captain Marvel is also supposed to play a big role in Avengers 4. She could start up TAHITI again with her blood and bring back any non-dusted heroes (Like Gamora, Hiemdall, or, not very likely, Loki.) We’ll just have to wait and see.
